<h1 class="hero-h">What is demand generation? <em>plain-English answer.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Demand generation is one of the most-used and least-precisely-defined terms in B2B marketing. Some teams use it interchangeably with lead generation; others mean something much broader. Here's the practical 2026 definition.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">The short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Demand generation is the function that creates awareness and interest in your category and brand, generating both inbound leads and the conditions for sales-led motion to succeed. Distinct from lead generation (which focuses on capturing existing demand). Demand gen owns: content, SEO, paid, events, partnerships, PR, and the metrics that show category presence. Typical demand gen budget: 8-15% of revenue at B2B mid-market.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
